# dev-import.sql — schema change safety

[`dev-import.sql`](../../src/main/resources/dev-import.sql) runs on **every** `%dev` startup via [`DatabaseDevSetup`](../../src/main/java/dev/vepo/issues/infra/DatabaseDevSetup.java), after Flyway applies migrations. **Any schema change must not break that script** — treat migration + `dev-import.sql` as one deliverable.

## Protected baseline

Dev personas used in tests and manual exploration:

| Asset | Why |
|-------|-----|
| `admin@issues.vepo.dev` | Admin role, user CRUD tests |
| `pm@issues.vepo.dev` | Project manager, project CRUD |
| `user@issues.vepo.dev` | Default ticket workflows |
| Sample project with prefix `ISS` | Kanban and ticket identifier tests |

Do not delete these users or the primary sample project without updating tests and [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md).

## When you change the schema (Flyway)

**Pre-production:** amend [`V1.0.0__Database_Creation.sql`](../../src/main/resources/db/migration/V1.0.0__Database_Creation.sql) only — see [issues-flyway.mdc](issues-flyway.mdc). Do not add `V1.0.x` migration files.

Work through this list **in the same PR** as the schema change:

1. **Reset section** — Extend TRUNCATE/DELETE in FK-safe order for tables dev seed repopulates.
2. **Seed section** — New `NOT NULL` columns or FKs require matching INSERT values.
3. **Verify** — Restart `mvn quarkus:dev` and confirm `DatabaseDevSetup` runs without SQL errors.

## TRUNCATE CASCADE trap

PostgreSQL `TRUNCATE parent CASCADE` truncates every table with an FK to `parent`. Clear inbound FKs first, then delete children; never assume CASCADE stops at intended tables.

## Quick checklist

- [ ] Reset section covers new dev-populated tables
- [ ] Inserts satisfy new NOT NULL and FK constraints
- [ ] Protected dev personas still exist after reset
- [ ] `%dev` startup completes with `dev-import.sql` executing successfully
